narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: DS Spring Lit is amazing. I would take it simply for the texts, but the DS Lit profs also tend to be really wonderful teachers who know how to lead a section. Almost every single lecture this semester was phenomenal. Even though it's true that the work load is much heavier than in the fall, it's worth it, and these texts are a joy to read.
Yes, definitely recommend. DS Lit in the spring is very different from DS Lit fall.
This class is a lot of work but ultimately rewarding.

I highly recommend taking both semesters of DS particularly because of the Literature track - Petrarch's Sonnets, Shakespeare's King Lear, Tolstoy's War and Peace, and Woolf's To the Lighthouse will truly change your life!
A survey of some of the great modern literary works, absolutely worth taking, not only for those majoring in the humanities, but for humans in general.

A survey of the Western Canon in literary works. I would recommend this class if you're interested in tracing the development of literature over time, and if you're an avid reader who thrives on devouring books quickly.
